# Build artefacts
/target/
**/target/

# `Cargo.lock` is COMMITTED. Rationale: octos-app ships a binary (`app/`)
# in addition to library crates; for binary-first workspaces Cargo
# documentation recommends checking the lockfile in so contributors and
# CI build against identical dep graphs. See cargo-book § "Cargo.lock".

# Local environment / secrets
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Editor / IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# macOS metadata
.DS_Store

# Note: `~/.config/octos-app/server.json` lives outside the repo (in the
# user's XDG config dir) so it does not need an entry here.
